ame <i>Maud</i> became quite common in England in the 19th century, when its popularity was influenced in part by  Tennyson's  poem Maud, published in  1855 , but has not been much used since the early decades of the 20th century."],"variants":[]},{"name":"of","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Short form of   Oswald   or any of the various other names beginning with <i>Os-</i>."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Maud of Stonegrave was born about 1138, in Stonegrave, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 son with William de Stonegrave."},"et":{"Abt 1138–Deceased":"umbes 1138–Surnud","1120–Male":"1120–Surnud","1180–Male":"1180–Surnud","1138–Female":"1138–Surnud","1138":"1138","Abt 1138":"umbes 1138","1120":"1120","1180":"1180","Stonegrave, Yorkshire, England.":"Stonegrave, Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1138–Deceased":"noin 1138–Kuollut","1120–Male":"1120–Kuollut","1180–Male":"1180–Kuollut","1138–Female":"1138–Kuollut","1138":"1138","Abt 1138":"noin 1138","1120":"1120","1180":"1180","Stonegrave, Yorkshire, England.":"Stonegrave, Yorkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1138–Deceased":"environ 1138–Décédée","1120–Male":"1120–Décédé","1180–Male":"1180–Décédé","1138–Female":"1138–Décédée","1138":"1138","Abt 1138":"environ 1138","1120":"1120","1180":"1180","Stonegrave, Yorkshire, England.":"Stonegrave, Everwyck, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Maud of Stonegrave est née environ 1138, à Stonegrave, Everwyck, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils avec William de Stonegrave."},"de":{"Abt 1138–Deceased":"um 1138–Verstorben","1120–Male":"1120–Verstorben","1180–Male":"1180–Verstorben","1138–Female":"1138–Verstorben","1138":"1138","Abt 1138":"um 1138","1120":"1120","1180":"1180","Stonegrave, Yorkshire, England.":"Stonegrave, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"Maud of Stonegrave wurde um 1138 in Stonegrave